    AssaultParty

    AssaultParty0Main
    Assault Party server of the Heist To The Museum.
    AssaultParty1Main
    Assault Party server of the Heist To The Museum.

    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent each Assault Party element, the identification of the thief, its position in the line to the room in the Museum and a number representing the carrying of a canvas.
    AssaultPartyInterface
    Stub to the Assault Party.
    AssaultPartyLogging
    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent each Assault Party, its room target and the constituting elements.

    General Repository server of the Heist To The Museum.

    The General Repository, where all information is stored and logged.

    General Repository server of the Heist To The Museum.
    HeistToTheMuseum
    Distributed version of the Heist To The Museum.
    Logger
    Logger responsible for generating and filling the logging file of the simulation.
    MasterThief
    Master Thief, the thief that commands the heist.

    MuseumInterface
    The Museum has rooms inside it.

    General Repository server of the Heist To The Museum.
    OrdinaryThief
    Ordinary Thief, one of the thieves involved in the heist.
    OrdinaryThiefLogging
    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent each Ordinary Thief, its identification, its situation and its maximum displacement.
    Register
    Operational interface of a remote object of type RegisterRemoteObject.
    RegisterRemoteObject
    Generic functionality to register in the local RMI registry service objects located in the same or other processing nodes of a parallel machine.
    ReturnBoolean
    Used for when a boolean value needs to be returned from a function where the state of one of the thieves is modified.
    Room
    Rooms contains paintings that can be stolen by the Thieves attacking the museum.
    RoomLogging
    Util class used in GeneralRepository to represent the rooms, their number of paintings and the distance to them.
    ServerRegisterRemoteObject
    Instantiation and registering of an object that enables the registration of other objects located in the same or other processing nodes of a parallel machine in the local RMI registry service.
